a and compares them with Art. 9 of the Uniform Commercial Code (U.S.) and suggests guiding principles for a European harmonization measure or national reform efforts. The book will assist market participants and their counsel to better understand secured transactions law and relevant private international law rules of their own and other countries and assist those involved in national, EU and global law reform efforts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aConflict of lawsxSecurityzEuropean Union countriesvCongresses. 0aSecurity (Law)zEuropean Union countriesvCongresses. 7aLAW / International.2bisacsh1 aBridge, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarrasco, Angel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDirix, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKieninger, Eva-Maria, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKieninger, Eva-Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeavy, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRakob, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSigman, Harry C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVeder, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVeneziano, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist History 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062100608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Law - 2000 - 2014z9783110636208oZDB-23-GLA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMP